    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.13-15_0001" />
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
           <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">SKYRIM FARM</hi>
                <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7</hi>
                <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>
           </fw>
                <opener>
                <dateline>2-3-'58</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Dr. Aly:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>During the past three days I have been hu<add>n</add>grily reading your <hi rend="underline">Hamilton</hi> &#8212; a fine experience; and I am most grateful to you. I wish you had put your name on the fly-leaf; but perhaps you will do so next summer.</p>
               
                <p>Surely the man emerges clearly from the pages of your book, and I am richer for knowing him better than before. Mrs. Aly remarked that I am <add>a</add> Hamiltonian, and I know what 
                    
                    <note type="authorial">-----
                                            over</note>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.13-15_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                    
                    she meant. Belief in functional farm &#8212; <hi rend="underline">cosmos!</hi> That's it! That 
                    was what was the matter with me when I was a Socialist. It has been the same with me in the conception of all values, from those of common sense up through esthetics, ethics, religion.</p>
               
                <p>You've done a lot of good, Aly. Many thanks!</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
            
